ENTRY       EC 1.3.1.96                 Enzyme
NAME        Botryococcus squalene synthase;
            SSL-2 (gene name)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-CH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     squalene:NADP+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    squalene + diphosphate + NADP+ = presqualene diphosphate + NADPH + H+ [RN:R02872]
ALL_REAC    R02872
SUBSTRATE   squalene [CPD:C00751];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     presqualene diphosphate [CPD:C03428];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     Isolated from the green alga Botryococcus braunii BOT22. Acts in the reverse direction. cf. EC 2.5.1.21, squalene synthase, where squalene is formed directly from farnesyl diphosphate.
HISTORY     EC 1.3.1.96 created 2012
